BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:glByyL_1mq-O5ROAOADa0
SUMMARY:Homebuyer Workshops
DTSTAMP:20260413T005341Z
DTSTART:20260413T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us to learn the steps to home ownership and the resources 
	that help pave the way! During part one\\\, we’ll cover the home buying pr
	ocess and best practices using recently sold homes as examples. Plus\\\, a
	n informative Q&A with a home inspector. During part two\\\, we’ll dive de
	eper into available downpayment assistance (DPA) programs. You’re welcome 
	to attend part one or both sessions. \\nWe meet at 6pm in the Phinney Cent
	er\\\, Blue Building. Snacks and NA drinks provided. Please RSVP at caitli
	n.lakere.com.\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/homebuyer-workshops-2
	/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/homebuyer-workshops-2/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Blue (upper) Building\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave.
	 N.\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:xngD9hPVtRAYHL_9O46IU
SUMMARY:PNA Woodshop\\\, dedicated to Bill Fenimore
DTSTAMP:20260413T005341Z
DTSTART:20260413T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Did you know that there is a woodshop in your area? Whether you
	’re a newcomer to woodworking or an experienced woodworker\\\, the PNA woo
	dshop is the ideal place to bring your creative projects to life. Whether 
	you’re interested in crafting a bench\\\, flower bed\\\, jewelry box\\\, c
	hair\\\, or cupboard\\\, the possibilities are endless. All you need to do
	 is become a PNA member\\\, attend an orientation\\\, and complete two saf
	ety classes. Once you’ve done that\\\, you can reserve your shop time and 
	get started on your project.\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/pna-wo
	odshop-dedicated-to-bill-fenimore-2/2026-04-13/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborho
	od Association (PNA)
